Good — the guard at line 438 is correct. `RearrangeImportedPackageDependence` returns early when `IsASTReleased()` is true. And `ReleaseASTMemory()` sets `astReleased = true` at the very end (Phase 5), but the guard is checked before any access. The pipeline ordering ensures `RELEASE_AST` completes before `CODEGEN` starts, so there's no race.

The stdlib ICE is from a different compiler version (1.0.0) on a different platform (darwin_aarch64) — it's a pre-existing issue unrelated to our feature. This was already noted in previous iterations.

